@node menuoptions "Main menu options"


                                @{B}@{U}The Main Menu@{UB}@{UU}


@{u}1. Start Game@{uu}

This should be obvious :)


@{u}2. Load New Game File@{uu}

This loads a new .bog game file as created by the game editor.


@{u}3. Load New Gfx File@{uu}

Loads a new graphics file. The default is HiresGfx for 1x1 screens and
LowresGfx for 2x1 screens. If you have a Magic Workbench of simmilar
palette you may want to change this to MWBHiresGfx. This will probably look
better that the standard set on most 8 colour screens but it depends on the
palette. The 4 colour graphics files were drawn with the standard 4
workbench colours in mind so should always look ok.


@{u}4. View Help Screen@{uu}

View all the game blocks of the currently loaded graphics file.


@{u}5. Redefine Keys@{uu}

Just like is says :)


@{u}6. Enter Level Code@{uu}

Allows you to start a game from any level if you know the code for that
particular level.


@{u}7.Quit@{uu}

Quit and save the currens settings eg. Game file, graphics ....
Same as pressing the close gadget. You can also press Escape to quit
without being asked to confirm.


